    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>That method can't return <code>true</code>.  That's the <em>point</em> of <code>Long.MAX_VALUE</code>.  It would be <em>really</em> confusing if its name were...  false.  Then it should be just called <code>Long.SOME_FAIRLY_LARGE_VALUE</code> and have literally zero reasonable uses.  Just use <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/q/13375357/1339987\">Android's <code>isUserAGoat</code></a>, or you may roll your own function that always returns <code>false</code>.</p>\n\n<p>Note that a <code>long</code> in memory takes a fixed number of bytes.  <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/datatypes.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">From Oracle</a>:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>long: The long data type is a 64-bit signed two's complement integer. It has a minimum value of -9,223,372,036,854,775,808 and a maximum value of 9,223,372,036,854,775,807 (inclusive). Use this data type when you need a range of values wider than those provided by int.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>As you may know from basic computer science or discrete math, there are 2^64 possible values for a long, since it is 64 bits.  And as you know from discrete math or number theory or common sense, if there's only finitely many possibilities, one of them has to be the largest.  That would be <code>Long.MAX_VALUE</code>.  So you are asking something similar to \"is there an integer that's >0 and &lt; 1?\"  Mathematically nonsensical.</p>\n\n<p>If you actually need this for something for real then use <code>BigInteger</code> class.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 62810,
      "reputation" : 5773,
      "user_id" : 186338,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 95,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/57d3d73f39c67905de18935eea4a3d7b?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "James Cronen",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/186338/james-cronen"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 14,
    "last_activity_date" : 1368542234,
    "creation_date" : 1368542234,
    "answer_id" : 16546084,
    "question_id" : 16546038,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can't. If you have a method called <code>isBiggerThanMaxLong(long)</code> it should always return <code>false</code>.</p>\n\n<p>If you were to increment the bits of <code>Long.MAX_VALUE</code>, the next value should be <code>Long.MIN_VALUE</code>. Read up on twos-complement and that should tell you why.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1190755,
      "reputation" : 49532,
      "user_id" : 1163607,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 97,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/egnaW.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "AllTooSir",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1163607/alltoosir"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 6,
    "last_activity_date" : 1763621435,
    "last_edit_date" : 1763621435,
    "creation_date" : 1368542344,
    "answer_id" : 16546128,
    "question_id" : 16546038,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Firstly, the below method doesn't compile as it is missing the return type and it should be <code>Long.MAX_VALUE</code> in place of <code>Long.Max_value</code>.</p>\n<pre><code>public static boolean isBiggerThanMaxLong(long value) {\n      return value &gt; Long.Max_value;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>The above method can never return  <code>true</code> as you are comparing a <code>long</code> value with <code>Long.MAX_VALUE</code> , see the method signature you can pass only <code>long</code> there.Any <code>long</code> can be as big as the <code>Long.MAX_VALUE</code>, it can't be bigger than that.</p>\n<p>You can try something like this with <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/math/BigInteger.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">BigInteger</a> class :</p>\n<pre><code>public static boolean isBiggerThanMaxLong(BigInteger l){\n    return l.compareTo(BigInteger.valueOf(Long.MAX_VALUE))==1;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>The below code will return <code>true</code> :</p>\n<pre><code>BigInteger big3 = BigInteger.valueOf(Long.MAX_VALUE).\n                  add(BigInteger.valueOf(Long.MAX_VALUE));\nSystem.out.println(isBiggerThanMaxLong(big3)); // prints true\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
